---
import Header from "../components/header.svelte";
import Layout from './layouts/Layout.astro'
---
<Layout>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/blogicon.png" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <!--Icons-->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/about.css" />
    <title>About | Chancellor Ceti</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
                I'm a high school senior, heading towards doing a bachelor's degree majoring in physics. I enjoy studying physics, math, and history. In my down time, I like watching films, reading, listening to music, and learning about the world.
      <br />
      <p>
                I use Rust 🦀 for most of my programming projects, but I also sometimes code in C, Python, Javascript, and Julia.
                You can find most of my recent work at <a href="https://github.com/ChancellorCeti" class="link">my github page here</a>.
                <br/>
            </p>
      <p>
            <p>
                Since my taste in films reflects part of who I am, I've attempted to construct <a href="/movies-and-tv/" class="link">a list of all the movies and TV shows I've ever seen over here</a>. I'm trying to start posting film reviews here, but until then, you can check out this page to see what all I've watched.</p>

            <p> I enjoy reading about history, especially the Cold War era, post-independence India, and West Bengal. I also like discussions about politics (mainly US and Indian), international relations, and economics.</p>

            <p>I like reading fiction and poetry; some random favorites are Hwang Sok-yong's "Mater 2-10," Rohinton Mistry's "A Fine Balance," Sukanta Bhattacharya's "Lenin," Roberto Bolaño's "2666," Neruda's "Walking Around," and Steinbeck's "The Grapes of Wrath." Music is a 24/7 presence in my life, usually alternating between rock and kpop. Some rock favorites are Nothing But Thieves (best group ever), The Doors, Pink Floyd, Dire Straits, Radiohead, Bruce Springsteen, U2, Royal Blood, The Black Keys, and Los Prisioneros; a few kpop favorites are NMIXX, BABYMONSTER, NewJeans, Aespa, Hearts2Hearts, RESCENE, and IVE. </p>

            <p>I follow many blogs, columnists, youtube channels, etc and think people are better at recommending media than algorithms are. In that spirit, I've begun compiling <a href="/recommended-content">a list of recommendations over here</a></p>

            <p>For contact purposes, I'm most active on my discord account <code
          >floofydoggo</code
                >
                <br/>
                <br/>
                I also have the email address <code>chancellorceti at gmail.com</code> but I check this infrequently.
      </p>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</Layout>
